# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in values before running the app.

```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
```

Variables are validated at runtime in `src/lib/env/schema.ts`.

---

## Required (all environments)

These must be set for the app to start and for admin operations to work.

### Client — exposed to the browser

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-publishable-key
```

### Server

```env
SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=your-supabase-secret-key
```

- `SITE_URL` — canonical base URL (use production domain on Vercel, e.g. `https://dhruvil.work`)
- `ADMIN_EMAIL` — must match the admin user in Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Users
- `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` — server-only; required for admin CMS, RLS bypass, and AI key encryption fallback

---

## Required in production only

Without these, public APIs are vulnerable or rate limiting is ineffective on Vercel.

```env
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://your-db.upstash.io
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=your-upstash-token
```

Create a free database at [upstash.com](https://upstash.com). Without Upstash, rate limiting falls back to in-memory (non-functional across serverless instances).

Also set `SITE_URL` to your production domain and align **CMS → Settings → site_url** with the same value.

---

## Optional — features

### AI providers (at least one needed for assistant/copilot)

```env
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
NVIDIA_API_KEY=

# Encrypts CMS-stored provider keys (falls back to SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY if unset)
AI_KEYS_ENCRYPTION_SECRET=
```

### Email (contact form / newsletter)

```env
RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_resend_api_key
EMAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=portfolio@example.com
EMAIL_REPLY_TO_ADDRESS=portfolio@example.com
```

### Feature flags

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_SEARCH=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_NEWSLETTER=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_AI_DEMOS=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_PORTFOLIO_ASSISTANT=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_PUBLIC_NOTES=false
```

### Analytics (PostHog)

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=phc_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.posthog.com
POSTHOG_API_KEY=phx_your_personal_api_key
POSTHOG_PROJECT_ID=
```

### Monitoring (Sentry)

```env
SENTRY_DSN=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=
```

Recommended for production error tracking and source map uploads.

---

## Development-only notes

- `SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000` is correct for local dev
- Upstash is optional locally (in-memory rate limiting works on a single process)
- Do not run `npm run db:seed` against production

---

## Pre-deploy verification

After configuring Vercel environment variables:

1. Visit `/admin/launch` — all critical checks should pass
2. Visit `/admin/system` — same checks, live health view
3. Confirm `SITE_URL` matches CMS `site_url` (no "SEO Configuration Mismatch")
4. Confirm Upstash is configured (no "Production Rate Limiting Disabled")

See `docs/deployment-checklist.md` for the full checklist.
